395
00:14:36,108 --> 00:14:37,376
CHOIR:
♪ On our show, on our show ♪

396
00:14:37,376 --> 00:14:39,378
♪ Now here is the man
to explain ♪

397
00:14:39,378 --> 00:14:41,313
♪ The tortured terrain
of your brain ♪

398
00:14:41,313 --> 00:14:44,450
♪ The man who feels
everyone's pain: ♪

399
00:14:44,450 --> 00:14:46,385
♪ Dr. Crane! ♪

400
00:14:46,385 --> 00:14:47,686
♪ Dr. Crane! ♪

401
00:14:47,686 --> 00:14:54,560
♪ Frasier Crane! ♪

402
00:14:54,560 --> 00:14:55,761
(dings)

403
00:14:57,930 --> 00:14:59,832
Way to go, Leon!

404
00:15:01,834 --> 00:15:02,735
Well, Kenny,

405
00:15:02,735 --> 00:15:05,804
what's your reaction?

406
00:15:08,574 --> 00:15:09,842
Wow.

407
00:15:09,842 --> 00:15:12,578
Takes your breath away,
doesn't it?

408
00:15:12,578 --> 00:15:13,879
Wow.

409
00:15:13,879 --> 00:15:14,780
I thought as much,

410
00:15:14,780 --> 00:15:16,782
and in anticipation
of your approval,

411
00:15:16,782 --> 00:15:18,284
I had the forethought

412
00:15:18,284 --> 00:15:19,785
to order in a
little bubbly.

413
00:15:19,785 --> 00:15:21,287
Niles, if you would
help me, please.

414
00:15:21,287 --> 00:15:22,788
(laughing):
You were wonderful!

415
00:15:22,788 --> 00:15:25,291
Thank you.
The trombone
frightened me.

416
00:15:27,092 --> 00:15:27,860
Wow.

417
00:15:27,860 --> 00:15:30,362
That was sure something,
wasn't it?

418
00:15:30,362 --> 00:15:31,330
I'll say.

419
00:15:31,330 --> 00:15:35,200
Sort of like Gilbert
and Sullivan-- only frightening.

420
00:15:35,200 --> 00:15:38,437
A little jingle,
that's all we wanted.

421
00:15:38,437 --> 00:15:40,806
Ten seconds to
start the show.

422
00:15:40,806 --> 00:15:43,309
Maybe Frasier
can cut this down.

423
00:15:43,309 --> 00:15:45,811
He gives me harps
and drums and...

424
00:15:45,811 --> 00:15:47,613
people speaking German.

425
00:15:47,613 --> 00:15:49,415
All we wanted was
a simple little jingle.

426
00:15:49,415 --> 00:15:51,784
Probably more like the one
you came up with.

427
00:15:51,784 --> 00:15:53,285
Tell him yours,
Mr. Crane.

428
00:15:53,285 --> 00:15:54,787
No, no, no.
It was nothing.

429
00:15:54,787 --> 00:15:56,288
I can't even remember
how it goes.

430
00:15:56,288 --> 00:15:57,289
Well, I do.

431
00:15:57,289 --> 00:15:59,692
♪ How are you? I'm listen... ♪

432
00:15:59,692 --> 00:16:01,593
It doesn't go like that.

433
00:16:01,593 --> 00:16:03,595
Well, then,
you sing it,
Mr. Crane.

434
00:16:04,096 --> 00:16:05,097
Well, all right.

435
00:16:05,097 --> 00:16:07,599
But, you know, it's
really nothing.

436
00:16:07,599 --> 00:16:10,102
♪ What's new? I'm listenin' ♪

437
00:16:10,102 --> 00:16:12,604
♪ Feelin' blue? I'm listenin' ♪

438
00:16:12,604 --> 00:16:13,906
♪ Feelin' sad, feelin' mad ♪

439
00:16:13,906 --> 00:16:15,374
♪ Feelin' bad, feelin' glad? ♪

440
00:16:15,374 --> 00:16:17,376
♪ I'm listenin'. ♪

441
00:16:17,376 --> 00:16:20,412
That's exactly the kind
of thing we're looking for!

442
00:16:20,412 --> 00:16:21,914
You know,
it sets the mood.

443
00:16:21,914 --> 00:16:22,915
It-it says it all.

444
00:16:22,915 --> 00:16:24,917
Did that just pop
into you head?

445
00:16:24,917 --> 00:16:27,219
Hardly.

446
00:16:27,219 --> 00:16:29,021
It was gut-wrenching,

447
00:16:29,021 --> 00:16:32,958
but, you know, it's nice to know
that I made it look easy.

448
00:16:32,958 --> 00:16:36,395
No, no, no. I'm talking
about your dad's little jingle.

449
00:16:36,395 --> 00:16:37,396
Dad's?

450
00:16:37,396 --> 00:16:38,897
Yeah, yeah, yeah,
he just sang it.

451
00:16:38,897 --> 00:16:40,366
It's exactly the type
of thing we need.

452
00:16:40,366 --> 00:16:41,867
You know, simple, catchy.

453
00:16:41,867 --> 00:16:43,869
You know, we ought
to just use that one.

454
00:16:43,869 --> 00:16:45,237
FRASIER:
No, no, no.
Kenny, no.

455
00:16:45,237 --> 00:16:46,605
No, if simple is
what you wanted,

456
00:16:46,605 --> 00:16:48,007
you should've
just said so.

457
00:16:48,007 --> 00:16:49,408
I thought I did.

458
00:16:49,408 --> 00:16:50,676
Obviously not.

459
00:16:50,676 --> 00:16:51,944
Now that I know what you want,

460
00:16:51,944 --> 00:16:52,945
well, there's nothing easier.

461
00:16:52,945 --> 00:16:53,946
Of course I can write simple.

462
00:16:54,446 --> 00:16:56,448
I promise you, it'll be
something far more memorable

463
00:16:56,448 --> 00:16:57,816
than what my dad came up with.

464
00:16:57,816 --> 00:16:59,685
Well, I don't know.
I remember it.

465
00:16:59,685 --> 00:17:01,687
♪ What's new? I'm listenin' ♪

466
00:17:01,687 --> 00:17:04,523
(choir joins in):
♪ Feel blue? I'm listenin' ♪

467
00:17:04,523 --> 00:17:06,258
♪ Feelin' sad, feelin' mad ♪

468
00:17:06,258 --> 00:17:08,160
♪ Feelin' bad, feelin' glad? ♪

469
00:17:08,160 --> 00:17:09,661
♪ I'm listenin'. ♪

470
00:17:12,097 --> 00:17:14,600
You're off
the clock!

