(playing
"Row, Row, Row Your Boat")

474
00:17:35,621 --> 00:17:36,588
Hi, Fras.

475
00:17:36,588 --> 00:17:38,457
How's it going?

476
00:17:38,457 --> 00:17:40,793
"Merrily, merrily."

477
00:17:40,793 --> 00:17:42,694
Well, now, it's getting
kind of late.

478
00:17:42,694 --> 00:17:44,196
Maybe you should call it
a night, huh?

479
00:17:44,696 --> 00:17:45,697
Dad, you heard Kenny.

480
00:17:45,697 --> 00:17:47,199
I have to come up
with something

481
00:17:47,199 --> 00:17:48,667
as simple as yours
by Monday.

482
00:17:48,667 --> 00:17:50,135
By the way, thanks, once again

483
00:17:50,135 --> 00:17:51,603
for completely upstaging me
today.

484
00:17:51,603 --> 00:17:53,572
Oh, come on.
I'm sorry I stole your thunder,

485
00:17:53,572 --> 00:17:55,374
but it's not like I did it
on purpose.

486
00:17:55,374 --> 00:17:56,208
I know, I know.

487
00:17:56,208 --> 00:17:57,676
I'm sorry. It's just...

488
00:17:57,676 --> 00:18:00,712
I don't know why I'm having
such a hard time with this.

489
00:18:00,712 --> 00:18:01,713
Well...

490
00:18:01,713 --> 00:18:03,715
maybe you're just thinking
too much.

491
00:18:03,715 --> 00:18:05,217
You know, look at me--

492
00:18:05,217 --> 00:18:07,219
I go to bathroom,
I'm flossing my teeth

493
00:18:07,219 --> 00:18:08,720
and that song pops
in my head.

494
00:18:08,720 --> 00:18:12,624
Are you suggesting that
I bring out a spool of floss?

495
00:18:12,624 --> 00:18:14,526
Well, it might not be a bad idea

496
00:18:15,027 --> 00:18:16,361
for a couple of reasons.

497
00:18:16,361 --> 00:18:19,064
Frasier, why don't you
just decide

498
00:18:19,064 --> 00:18:20,933
what you want to say
and say it

499
00:18:20,933 --> 00:18:23,435
without a lot of big words
and showing off.

500
00:18:23,435 --> 00:18:26,438
You know, and the tune
should be something simple,

501
00:18:26,438 --> 00:18:27,806
something you can whistle.

502
00:18:27,806 --> 00:18:29,675
I tried whistling that thing
you wrote today,

503
00:18:29,675 --> 00:18:32,678
and I got light-headed.

504
00:18:34,012 --> 00:18:35,347
Of course it might've
been that last doughnut.

505
00:18:35,347 --> 00:18:38,851
I went back for one of those
African rain sticks.

506
00:18:41,787 --> 00:18:45,290
The truth is, Dad, I

507
00:18:45,290 --> 00:18:48,560
I'm not sure I can do simple.

508
00:18:48,560 --> 00:18:50,796
Well, I don't know if you can't
or if you just don't want to.

509
00:18:50,796 --> 00:18:52,731
But some of the best things
in the world

510
00:18:52,731 --> 00:18:54,099
are simple, Fras.

511
00:18:54,099 --> 00:18:55,501
Just like that art gallery
you took me to

