00:18:59,505 --> 00:19:02,407
over this painting
of a big, red dot.

516
00:19:02,407 --> 00:19:05,244
Yeah, Dad. But there is a
difference between simple

517
00:19:05,244 --> 00:19:08,046
and deceptively simple.

518
00:19:08,046 --> 00:19:10,315
Well, all I'm saying is
that it's fine to be smart,

519
00:19:10,315 --> 00:19:13,118
but you shouldn't have
to be proving it all the time,

520
00:19:13,118 --> 00:19:13,919
that's all.

521
00:19:13,919 --> 00:19:15,687
You know,
just as an experiment,

522
00:19:15,687 --> 00:19:17,489
tell me what it is
you're trying to say

523
00:19:17,489 --> 00:19:19,825
stripped down to nuts and bolts.

524
00:19:21,593 --> 00:19:23,128
All right, um...

525
00:19:23,128 --> 00:19:26,632
in my first stanza,
I want to represent myself

526
00:19:26,632 --> 00:19:29,635
as the... ombudsman
between the conscious

527
00:19:30,102 --> 00:19:33,038
and subconscious minds
of my listeners.

528
00:19:33,038 --> 00:19:34,439
Ah. Well, there you are.

529
00:19:34,940 --> 00:19:36,441
There's the song right there.

530
00:19:36,441 --> 00:19:38,944
All we need
is a rhyme for "ombudsman,"

531
00:19:38,944 --> 00:19:40,846
and we can go to bed.

532
00:19:40,846 --> 00:19:44,316
I was playing around
with "north woodsman."

533
00:19:44,316 --> 00:19:45,684
(laughing)

534
00:19:45,684 --> 00:19:48,554
Oh, Frasier...

535
00:19:48,554 --> 00:19:50,956
Look, I'm going to tell you
what your show's about:

536
00:19:50,956 --> 00:19:53,425
People have a problem,
they're feeling low,

537
00:19:53,425 --> 00:19:55,360
they call you,
you make them feel better.

538
00:19:55,360 --> 00:19:56,261
Oh, for God's sake, Dad.

539
00:19:56,261 --> 00:19:57,563
Well, that's it,
that's it.

540
00:19:57,563 --> 00:19:59,331
Why don't you just write
about that?

541
00:19:59,331 --> 00:20:00,632
How would that
sound exactly?

542
00:20:00,632 --> 00:20:02,501
♪ If you've got a problem,
if you're feeling low ♪

543
00:20:02,501 --> 00:20:03,502
♪ Looking for some answers... ♪

544
00:20:03,502 --> 00:20:05,504
Oh, gosh, now I'm stuck.

545
00:20:05,504 --> 00:20:08,006
How will I ever find
a rhyme for "low"?

546
00:20:08,006 --> 00:20:09,007
Okay, smart aleck.

547
00:20:09,007 --> 00:20:10,509
I was just trying to help.

548
00:20:10,509 --> 00:20:11,810
Well, thanks, Dad.

549
00:20:11,810 --> 00:20:13,612
I'm sorry. It's
just not my thing.

550
00:20:13,612 --> 00:20:17,115
Okay, well,
I'm going to bed.

551
00:20:17,115 --> 00:20:19,618
So, if you need
any help tomorrow,

552
00:20:19,618 --> 00:20:21,119
all you got to do is ask.

553
00:20:21,119 --> 00:20:23,121
Thanks, Dad.

554
00:20:34,433 --> 00:20:36,935
(plays a note)

555
00:20:37,936 --> 00:20:41,440
♪ If you've got a problem ♪

556
00:20:41,440 --> 00:20:45,944
